  "prompt": "What can substitute butter in a brownies recipe?",
  "response": "If you're looking to substitute butter in a brownie recipe, there are several options you can consider:\n\n1. **Vegetable Oil**: This is a common substitute for butter in brownie recipes. It provides moisture and a similar texture. Use the same amount of oil as you would butter.\n\n2. **Coconut Oil**: Coconut oil can be used in place of butter in equal amounts. It adds a subtle coconut flavor to the brownies.\n\n3. **Applesauce**: Unsweetened applesauce can be used as a healthier alternative. Replace butter with applesauce in a 1:1 ratio, though this may make the brownies slightly denser and chewier.\n\n4. **Greek Yogurt**: Plain Greek yogurt can add moisture and a slight tang to brownies. Substitute butter with Greek yogurt in a 1:1 ratio.\n\n5. **Avocado**: Mashed avocado can be used as a butter substitute. Use an equal amount of mashed avocado. It will add creaminess and some healthy fats without altering the flavor significantly.\n\n6. **Banana**: Mashed banana can be used as a substitute for butter. Use an equal amount, but keep in mind it will impart a banana flavor to the brownies.\n\n7. **Nut Butters**: Peanut butter, almond butter, or other nut butters can be used. They will add a nutty flavor to the brownies. Substitute in equal amounts.\n\n8. **Pumpkin Puree**: This can be a good substitute, particularly for a fall twist. Use in equal amounts as you would butter.\n\nRemember that each substitute may slightly alter the flavor and texture of your brownies, so you might want to experiment to find the one you like best.",
